    "title": {
      "rendered": "5 Tips to Craft Your Nonprofit&#8217;s Year-End Fundraising Campaigns"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p>Your nonprofit does incredible, life-changing work. Your year-end fundraising campaigns should show your donors what you\u2019ve accomplished together over the past year, and invite them to give toward an even brighter future.</p>\n<p>Excellent year-end campaigns need to strike a balance between hitting uplifting emotional beats that are relevant to your mission and delivering a compelling case for why people should support your nonprofit. Done well, your year-end campaigns (print, email, and social media) will inspire donors to give generously at year&#8217;s end and throughout the year after.</p>\n<header id=\"section-1-toc-2\" data-toc-subtag=\"Inspiring stories &amp; testimonials\">\n<h2>1. Include inspiring stories and testimonials</h2>\n</header>\n<p>Show your donors how their giving makes a difference for your mission. Pare down the most <a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/nonprofit-technology-blog/fundraising-software/the-secrets-of-nonprofit-storytelling-social-media-staffing-issues-beyond/?utm_source=NPTechForGood&amp;utm_medium=Paid_Link&amp;utm_campaign=Paid_Link-NPTechForGood\">inspiring stories</a> from the past year into bite-sized stories or quotes, and your donors will feel proud to be a part of your team.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/nonprofit-technology-blog/fundraising-software/the-secrets-of-nonprofit-storytelling-social-media-staffing-issues-beyond/?utm_source=NPTechForGood&amp;utm_medium=Paid_Link&amp;utm_campaign=Paid_Link-NPTechForGood\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-34058 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Fundraising-Quote-for-Appeals-e1665748531118.png?resize=800%2C332\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"332\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Fundraising-Quote-for-Appeals-e1665748531118.png?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Fundraising-Quote-for-Appeals-e1665748531118.png?resize=300%2C125&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Fundraising-Quote-for-Appeals-e1665748531118.png?resize=768%2C319&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Fundraising-Quote-for-Appeals-e1665748531118.png?resize=50%2C21&amp;ssl=1 50w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Fundraising-Quote-for-Appeals-e1665748531118.png?resize=600%2C250&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<header id=\"section-1-toc-3\" data-toc-subtag=\"Beautiful photos of donor impact\">\n<h2>2. Feature beautiful photos illustrating donor impact</h2>\n</header>\n<p>Pair your\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/nonprofit-technology-blog/featured/nonprofit-storytelling-fundamentals-from-executive-coaches-fundraising-experts/\">impact stories</a>\u00a0with high-quality photos showcasing the difference you make in your community. Even if your supporters don\u2019t take the time to read your letter all the way through (<a href=\"https://betterfundraising.com/lessons-from-a-heat-map/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">odds are, they won\u2019t!</a>), they\u2019ll see powerful images that will inspire them to give in a matter of seconds.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Year-End-appeal.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-34059\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Year-End-appeal.png?resize=800%2C375\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Year-End-appeal.png?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Year-End-appeal.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Year-End-appeal.png?resize=768%2C360&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/DonorPerfect-Year-End-appeal.png?resize=50%2C23&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<header id=\"section-1-toc-4\" data-toc-subtag=\"Compelling design\">\n<h2>3. Use compelling design</h2>\n</header>\n<p>Tie all of your year-end materials together by weaving a <a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/whitepapers/generic/design-tips-for-nonprofits/?utm_source=NPTechForGood&amp;utm_medium=Paid_Link&amp;utm_campaign=Paid_Link-NPTechForGood\">campaign-specific design</a> through everything your donors will see, including emails, your website, social media posts, and direct mail pieces.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/whitepapers/generic/design-tips-for-nonprofits/?utm_source=NPTechForGood&amp;utm_medium=Paid_Link&amp;utm_campaign=Paid_Link-NPTechForGood\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-34060\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Design-Tips-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=800%2C400\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Design-Tips-for-Nonprofits.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Design-Tips-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=300%2C150&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Design-Tips-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=768%2C384&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Design-Tips-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=50%2C25&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<header id=\"section-1-toc-5\" data-toc-subtag=\"A clear &amp; compelling CTA\">\n<h2>4. Include a clear and compelling call to action</h2>\n</header>\n<p>Give your supporters a simple and obvious path forward. It\u2019s critical to capture their energy in the moment, while they\u2019re excited and inspired to give.</p>\n<p>For emails, your\u00a0donate button\u00a0should be eye-catching with short and clear text. Even something as straightforward as \u201cGIVE NOW\u201d works well! For direct mail, include a reply device and return envelope so your donors don\u2019t have to track down an envelope or stamp at home. On social media, pair your posts with a link to your donation form.</p>\n<header id=\"section-1-toc-6\" data-toc-subtag=\"Multichannel Fundraising Strategies \">\n<h2>5. Embrace a multichannel fundraising strategy</h2>\n<p>Multichannel fundraising refers to reaching the same donors through multiple communication methods, or channels. For example, you might pair a direct mail appeal letter with a follow-up email that includes a <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/integrations/email-marketing/dpvideo/\">video</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">\u00a0or other interactive element.</span></p>\n</header>\n<p>Taking a multichannel approach to your year-end fundraising campaign can help you ensure that you reach as many donors as possible. Our <a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/nonprofit-technology-blog/fundraising-software/4-strategies-to-build-multichannel-donor-relationships/\">free 4 Strategies to Build Multichannel Donor Relationships guide</a> provides you with the tips and tools you need to prime all of your channels, from your website to your direct mail appeals, for maximum exposure and engagement.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/nonprofit-technology-blog/fundraising-software/4-strategies-to-build-multichannel-donor-relationships/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-34062 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/multichannel_fb_2-e1665767952340.gif?resize=800%2C420\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"420\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"background-color: #8362ae; padding: 4px;\"></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #efebeb; padding: 5px;\">\n<h2><strong> \u25ba </strong><b>About the Author</b></h2>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #efebeb; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #8362ae;\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/emilylefferts/\">Emily Lefferts</a> is a copywriter at <a style=\"color: #8362ae;\" href=\"https://www.donorperfect.com/\">DonorPerfect</a> \u2013 a top-rated donor management system and fundraising platform for nonprofits.</div>\n<hr />\n",
